&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an enthusiastic individual to work as Band 6 Deputy Ward Manager on the Mary Seacole ward 2 which is a 14 bed female acute Ward at the Mary Seacole house.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need positive interpersonal skills and commitment to work with adults within the field of mental health, and will be joining a hard-working multi-disciplinary team dedicated to achieving the best outcomes for Service users and Carers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For the successful candidate your line manager will in return provide you with support and supervision and will explore with you options for further development on the ward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will provide leadership towards the team, and will be heavily involved in quality initiatives, and implementing change that supports the trust strategy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameAngela EatlyTelephone number0121 301 6127&lt;/p&gt;
